case of a black man killing another one, just one, the whole time that I was growing up

1051
01:32:03,360 --> 01:32:07,320
and it was so traumatic that I had nightmares about it.

1052
01:32:07,320 --> 01:32:08,840
I only knew what are the men.

1053
01:32:08,840 --> 01:32:11,320
I knew the one who got killed.

1054
01:32:11,320 --> 01:32:16,440
And it went through our community like wildfire when this man was killed.

1055
01:32:16,440 --> 01:32:21,640
And now it's just so ordinary that you just don't, you hardly blink an eye when you

1056
01:32:21,640 --> 01:32:22,640
do about it, you know.

1057
01:32:22,640 --> 01:32:26,640
Drugs and gangs, imported from the North, they were, they weren't around.

1058
01:32:26,640 --> 01:32:27,640
Exactly.

1059
01:32:27,640 --> 01:32:28,640
Exactly.

1060
01:32:28,640 --> 01:32:32,400
Nobody knew anything about that kind of stuff.

1061
01:32:32,400 --> 01:32:35,760
Your children grew up in that time of transition.

1062
01:32:35,760 --> 01:32:37,000
This is the final question.

1063
01:32:37,000 --> 01:32:39,000
Talk about your kids, what do you do with it?

1064
01:32:39,080 --> 01:32:41,400
Okay, let me start with my oldest one.

1065
01:32:41,400 --> 01:32:42,720
His name is Earl.

1066
01:32:42,720 --> 01:32:45,000
He owns a small construction business.

1067
01:32:45,000 --> 01:32:47,680
So he's, you know, he works for himself.

1068
01:32:47,680 --> 01:32:49,800
He has a small crew.

1069
01:32:49,800 --> 01:32:54,040
Sometimes it's 10 people depending on the jobs that he gets and sometimes it's four or

1070
01:32:54,040 --> 01:32:55,560
five, you know.

1071
01:32:55,560 --> 01:33:00,560
So he lives in Madison, but you know, his business is in this area.

1072
01:33:00,560 --> 01:33:03,040
My next son is Orlando.

1073
01:33:03,040 --> 01:33:05,360
He's a fireman.

1074
01:33:05,360 --> 01:33:07,440
And so that's the major thing that he does.

1075
01:33:07,520 --> 01:33:08,520
Earl is married.

1076
01:33:08,520 --> 01:33:10,680
He has four children.

1077
01:33:10,680 --> 01:33:12,200
Orlando is also married.

1078
01:33:12,200 --> 01:33:14,040
He has three.

1079
01:33:14,040 --> 01:33:18,080
And my next son is Omar and he has a couple of kids.

1080
01:33:18,080 --> 01:33:19,680
He's not married.

1081
01:33:19,680 --> 01:33:23,600
And he is an IT specialist.

1082
01:33:23,600 --> 01:33:30,800
And his job was, was bought by another, I mean, his company was sold to another company.

1083
01:33:30,800 --> 01:33:33,680
So he lost his job three years ago.

1084
01:33:33,680 --> 01:33:37,000
At that point, he decided that he would go back to school.

1085
01:33:37,000 --> 01:33:39,360
I mean, he has a degree in political science.

1086
01:33:39,360 --> 01:33:41,520
He went to Rust College.

1087
01:33:41,520 --> 01:33:44,120
Orlando went to our Alcorn College.

1088
01:33:44,120 --> 01:33:49,560
Earl went to two years at high-end community college.

1089
01:33:49,560 --> 01:33:57,480
And Omar decided that he would go back and get a degree in engineering and computer engineering.

1090
01:33:57,480 --> 01:34:00,280
So he's getting close to finishing that up.

1091
01:34:00,280 --> 01:34:02,160
He's in Jackson State.

1092
01:34:02,160 --> 01:34:05,440
And then the next one is T, of course, T.

1093
01:34:05,440 --> 01:34:11,000
And she has a doctorate and she's teaching at the Ohio State University.

1094
01:34:11,000 --> 01:34:12,000
And then my youngest...

1095
01:34:12,000 --> 01:34:13,000
Has a book coming out?

1096
01:34:13,000 --> 01:34:17,760
As a book coming out, hopefully, within the next year or so.

1097
01:34:17,760 --> 01:34:20,240
And my youngest child is Jessica.

1098
01:34:20,240 --> 01:34:21,400
And she's an attorney.

1099
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:24,960
She graduated law school at Michigan.

1100
01:34:24,960 --> 01:34:29,080
And she's been an attorney now for, I think, seven years or so.

1101
01:34:29,080 --> 01:34:32,120
She worked for a local law firm here in Jackson.

1102
01:34:32,120 --> 01:34:34,680
And that's it.

1103
01:34:34,680 --> 01:34:35,680
You're Mr. Simpson.

1104
01:34:35,680 --> 01:34:37,880
Thank you very much for inviting us in.

1105
01:34:37,880 --> 01:34:40,120
This has been a wonderful time for me.

1106
01:34:40,120 --> 01:34:46,680
And I'm sure that the people at the museum and the many people who are going to be viewing

1107
01:34:46,680 --> 01:34:48,480
this will share my sympathy.

1108
01:34:48,480 --> 01:34:49,720
Well, John, thank you.

1109
01:34:49,720 --> 01:34:51,160
I'm so good to see you.

1110
01:34:51,160 --> 01:34:52,960
Yes, it is.

1111
01:34:52,960 --> 01:34:54,560
You're in this setting.

1112
01:34:54,560 --> 01:34:56,560
This setting, you know.

1113
